geonames.summary: Jurong East Bus Interchange (Simplified Chinese: 裕廊东巴士转换站 | Traditional Chinese: 裕廊東巴士轉換站) is a bus interchange located in Jurong East, Singapore. An open-air single-level bus terminal, it is directly connected to the adjacent Jurong East MRT Station (...)
geonames.title: Jurong East Bus Interchange

geonames.summary: IMM Shopping Mall or IMM Building (Chinese: 国际商品批发中心大厦) is a shopping centre located at Jurong East, Singapore. IMM is an abbreviation for "International Merchandise Mart". The shopping centre is managed by Capitaland. In 2007, IMM expanded and now has 3 new levels of shops (...)
geonames.title: IMM Shopping Mall

geonames.summary: Jurong East MRT Station (NS1/EW24) is an above-ground Mass Rapid Transit (MRT) station that is part of the North South Line (Branch Line before 1996) and the East West Line in Singapore, and serves as an interchange station between the two lines (...)
geonames.title: Jurong East MRT Station

geonames.summary: The Jurong Entertainment Centre (Chinese: 裕廊娱乐中心) was a shopping centre located in Jurong East, Singapore. It was closed and demolished and a new shopping mall named JCube is planned to replace it. The shopping centre was built in 1993, and has a net lettable retail floor area of  (...)
geonames.title: Jurong Entertainment Centre

geonames.summary: Jurong Regional Library (Chinese: 裕廊区域图书馆) is a public library located in Jurong East, Singapore. The last regional library to be completed after the Tampines and Woodlands regional libraries, it was upgraded on the site of the former Jurong East Community Library, the latter of which closed in 2002 (...)
geonames.title: Jurong Regional Library

geonames.summary: The Science Centre Singapore (Abbreviation: SCS, Chinese: 新加坡科学馆), previously known as Singapore Science Centre is a scientific institution in Jurong East, Singapore, specialising in the promotion of scientific and technological education for the general public (...)
geonames.title: Science Centre Singapore

geonames.summary: International Business Park (Abbreviation: IBP; Chinese: 国际商业园) is a high-tech business park managed by JTC Corporation in Jurong East, Singapore. Established in 1992, the International Business Park is Singapore's first business park (...)
geonames.title: International Business Park

geonames.summary: Jurong East is a town in the west region of Singapore. The town covers an area of 3.8 km² and is managed by the South West Community Development Council.  (...)
geonames.title: Jurong East

geonames.summary: Bukit View Secondary School (BtVSS) is a Government-funded secondary school, located in Bukit Batok, on the western part of Singapore. The school aimed to nurture creativity, passion and resilience in all her students to be people with moral integrity and are responsible to self and society.  (...)
geonames.title: Bukit View Secondary School

geonames.summary: Chinese Garden MRT Station (EW25) is an above-ground Mass Rapid Transit station on the East West Line in Singapore. It serves residents in Jurong East Neighbourhoods 2 and 3 and also the nearby Chinese Garden, which the station derives its name from (...)
geonames.title: Chinese Garden MRT Station

geonames.summary: Bukit Batok MRT Station (NS2) is an above-ground Mass Rapid Transit station on the North South Line in Singapore, and for six years part of the Branch Line until the opening of the Woodlands Extension. The station serves mainly residents of the Bukit Batok neighbourhood (...)
geonames.title: Bukit Batok MRT Station

geonames.summary: Millennia Institute (Abbreviation: MI; ; Abbreviated 励仁高中;) is the only Centralised Institute (CI) in Singapore. MI was established on 3 January 2004, to conglomerate the sparsely-organised three-year pre-university institutes into a single entity (...)
geonames.title: Millennia Institute

geonames.summary: Bukit Batok Community Library (BBCL) is located at Bukit Batok on the third floor of West Mall in Singapore. This is fifth library of the National Library Board that is located inside a shopping mall. The library was officially opened on 21 November 1998 by Deputy Prime Minister, BG (NS) Lee Hsien (...)
geonames.title: Bukit Batok Community Library

geonames.summary: West Mall is a shopping centre located in Bukit Batok, Singapore. Opening in 1998, the 8 story mall includes a total gross floor area of sitting on a land area of . West Mall houses a mix of retailers from fashion and accessory vendors, jewelery retailers, gifts and specialty stores, telcos, cafes (...)
geonames.title: West Mall

geonames.summary: Japanese Garden (Chinese: 星和园), also commonly known as Jurong Gardens, is a park in Jurong East, Singapore. It is built on an artificial island in the Jurong Lake area connected to the adjacent Chinese Garden island by bridge.
geonames.title: Japanese Garden, Singapore

geonames.summary: The Bukit Batok Interchange is located at Bukit Batok Central, near the West Mall Shopping Centre and the Bukit Batok MRT Station. The bus interchange was operated by SBS Transit till end 1999 and was given the operation to SMRT after that.  (...)
geonames.title: Bukit Batok Bus Interchange

geonames.summary: Jurong East Stadium is a multi-purpose stadium in Jurong East, Singapore. It is currently used mostly for football matches and is the home stadium of Albirex Niigata FC. The stadium holds 2,700 people and opened in 1998 (...)
geonames.title: Jurong East Stadium

geonames.summary: Jurong Lake (Chinese: 裕廊湖 ; ;) is a 70ha freshwater lake and reservoir located in the western region of Singapore formed with the damming of Sungei Jurong further downstream. The lake serves as a reservoir contributing to the water supply of the country (...)
geonames.title: Jurong Lake

geonames.summary: Ulu Pandan Depot is a depot near Jurong East, Singapore and it services the trains on the North South Line and the East West Line. It has a capacity of 40 trains (30 trains in service) and has an area of 130,000 square metres. Train inspection is carried out at this depot (...)
geonames.title: Ulu Pandan Depot

geonames.summary: Teban Gardens (population: approx 35,000) is a residential neighbourhood which is part of Jurong East New Town in the West Region of Singapore. Immediately north of Pandan Reservoir, it comprises exclusively of public housing built by the JTC Corporation and Housing Development Board.  (...)
geonames.title: Teban Gardens

geonames.summary: Fuhua Secondary School is a secondary school in Jurong West, Singapore. It started in 2000 and the founding principal was Ong Kian Choon. Oen Siew Yock took over as principal in 2005 when Ong was transferred to Nan Chiau High School (...)
geonames.title: Fuhua Secondary School

geonames.summary: Pandan Gardens (population: approx 19,000) is a residential neighbourhood which is part of Jurong East New Town in the West Region of Singapore. Immediately north of Pandan Reservoir and adjacent to Teban Gardens, it comprises exclusively of public housing built by the JTC Corporation.  (...)
geonames.title: Pandan Gardens

geonames.summary: Bukit Batok Town Park is a nature park located off Bukit Batok East Ave 5 created from a disused granite quarry. This park bears resemblance to Guilin in China, that is, a granite rock sitting within a lake. Hence it is also known as Little Guilin or Xiao Guilin among the locals.  (...)
geonames.title: Bukit Batok Town Park

geonames.summary: Little Guilin is a park in Bukit Gombak, Singapore. It is a popular visitor attraction due to its similarity to the scenery of Guilin, China.  (...)
geonames.title: Little Guilin

geonames.summary: Bukit Gombak MRT Station (NS3) is an above-ground Mass Rapid Transit station on the North South Line in Singapore. The station was opened on 10 March 1990. It was part of the Branch Line before the opening of the Woodlands Extension on 10 February 1996 (...)
geonames.title: Bukit Gombak MRT Station

geonames.summary: The Bukit Gombak Stadium is located in Bukit Batok, Singapore, and has a capacity of 3,000 people. The stadium was home to Gombak United FC in the S-league before they left the S-league in the year 2002. Thereafter, the stadium was converted to a Centre of Excellence for the Singapore Athletic (...)
geonames.title: Bukit Gombak Stadium

geonames.summary: Lakeside MRT Station (EW26) is an above-ground Mass Rapid Transit station on the East West Line in Singapore. As the Jurong Lake lies next to this station which derived its name from geographical feature, it serves the residents living in Jurong West Neighbourhoods 1 to 5.  (...)
geonames.title: Lakeside MRT Station

geonames.summary: Jurong Stadium is a multi-purpose stadium in Jurong, Singapore. It is currently used mostly for football matches and was the home stadium of Sinchi FC when they played in the S.League from 2003 to 2005. Previously, Singapore Armed Forces FC had played their home games in this venue (...)
geonames.title: Jurong Stadium

geonames.summary: Dunearn Secondary School (abbreviation: DSS) is a government secondary school located at Bukit Batok, Singapore. The school provides Express, Normal Academic/Technical courses from Secondary 1 to Secondary 5 levels.  (...)
geonames.title: Dunearn Secondary School

geonames.summary: Pandan Reservoir (Simplified Chinese: 班丹蓄水池) is a reservoir located in the West Region of Singapore. Formed by damming the mouth of Sungei Pandan, it is the largest service reservoir in Singapore providing non-potable water to the surrounding industrial areas and in particular, the Jurong Industrial (...)
geonames.title: Pandan Reservoir

geonames.summary: The Bukit Batok Memorial is located on top of the tranquil Bukit Batok Hill upon which once stood two war memorials built by Australian POWs to commemorate the war dead of the Japanese and the Allies who fought during the decisive Battle of Bukit Timah in Singapore during the Second World War (...)
geonames.title: Bukit Batok Memorial

geonames.summary: The monkey tree phenomenon is a social phenomenon in Singapore, which began in September 2007. It arose from the discovery of a callus on a tree in Jurong West New Town, which appears monkey-like. The callus has initiated a minor social mania, drawing large crowds to look or pray at the tree.  (...)
geonames.title: Monkey tree phenomenon

geonames.summary: Rail transport in Singapore exists in three main types, namely an international rail connection operated by Malaysian company Keretapi Tanah Melayu(KTM), a rapid transit system collectively known as the Mass Rapid Transit (MRT) system operated by the two biggest public transport operators SMRT (...)
geonames.title: Rail transport in Singapore

geonames.summary: The Old Ford Motor Factory (Chinese: 旧福特汽车工厂) is a historic building in Singapore, located along Upper Bukit Timah Road.  (...)
geonames.title: Old Ford Motor Factory
